The paper discusses using tensor factorization to learn more compact representations for reinforcement learning policies, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of biologically inspired architectures also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The evaluation of the approach on the Atari suite suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV), and the use of second order optimization and wavelet scattering suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
